019}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! Activity\n! Total\n|-\n|Agriculture, forestry and fishing||align=\"right\"|59\n|-\n|Mining and quarrying||align=\"right\"|870\n|-\n|Manufacturing||align=\"right\"|341\n|-\n|Electricity, gas, steam and air conditioning supply||align=\"right\"|23\n|-\n|Water supply; sewerage, waste management and remediation activities||align=\"right\"|30\n|-\n|Construction||align=\"right\"|14\n|-\n|Wholesale and retail trade, repair of motor vehicles and motorcycles||align=\"right\"|113\n|-\n|Transportation and storage||align=\"right\"|73\n|-\n|Accommodation and food services||align=\"right\"|32\n|-\n|Information and communication||align=\"right\"|10\n|-\n|Financial and insurance activities||align=\"right\"|40\n|-\n|Real estate activities||align=\"right\"|-\n|-\n|Professional, scientific and technical activities||align=\"right\"|23\n|-\n|Administrative and support service activities||align=\"right\"|5\n|-\n|Public administration and defense; compulsory social security||align=\"right\"|115\n|-\n|Education||align=\"right\"|128\n|-\n|Human health and social work activities||align=\"right\"|56\n|-\n|Arts, entertainment and recreation||align=\"right\"|11\n|-\n|Other service activities||align=\"right\"|14\n|- class=\"sortbottom\"\n|'''Total'''||align=\"right\"|'''1,957'''\n|}\n\n==Sports==\nThe local football team, [[FK Boksit Mili\u0107i]], were also established by the company in 1972.\n\nIn the 1990s, businessman Rajko Duki\u0107 invested in sports development in Mili\u0107i, and local teams became champions of Republika Srpska in football, chess, bowling and women's handball. He also invested in a large cultural complex occupying the centre of the town, including a museum, motel, pool complex and the 65-metre tall 'Rajko's Tower'.<ref>http://lat.rtrs.tv/vijesti/vijest/miliciotvoren-toranj-i-muzej-rudarstva-13146</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Municipalities of Republika Srpska]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n* Official results from the book ''Ethnic composition of Bosnia-Herzegovina population, by municipalities and settlements, 1991''. Census, Zavod za statistiku Bosne i Hercegovine - Bilten no.234, Sarajevo 1991.\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Mili\u0107i}}\n\n{{Political divisions of Bosnia and Herzegovina}}\n\n[[Category:Populated places in Mili\u0107i, Republika Srpska]]\n[[Category:Municipalities of Republika Srpska]]\n\n{{Mili\u0107i-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{redirect|Mili\u0107i, Bosnia and Herzegovina|the village near Banovi\u0107i|Mili\u0107i (Banovi\u0107i)}}\n{{Infobox settlement <!--more fields are available for this Infobox--See Template:Infobox Settlement-->\n| native_name                     = \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0438\u045b\u0438\n| official_name                   = Mili\u0107i\n| other_name                      = \n| image_shield                    = Mili\u0107i (grb).svg\n| image_map                       = Mili\u0107i municipality.svg\n| settlement_type                 = [[List of cities in Bosnia and Herzegovina|Town]] and [[Municipalities of Republika Srpska|municipality]]\n| subdivision_type                = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n| subdivision_name                = [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Political divisions of Bosnia and Herzegovina|Entity]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Republika Srpska]]\n| subdivision_type2               = \n| subdivision_name2               = \n| parts                           = 54\n| leader_title                    = [[Mayor]]\n| leader_name                     = Momir Lazarevi\u0107\n| leader_party                    = [[Alliance of Independent Social Democrats|SNSD]]\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| map_caption                     = Location of Mili\u0107i within Bosnia and Herzegovina\n| population_as_of                = 2013 census\n| area_total_km2                  = 279.13\n| population_total                = 11441\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|44|09|58|N|19|04|30|E|region:BA_type:adm2nd|display=inline, title}}\n| timezone                        = [[Central European Time|CET]]\n| utc_offset                      = +1\n| timezone_DST                    = [[Central European Summer Time|CEST]]\n| utc_offset_DST                  = +2\n| area_code                       = 56\n| website                         = \n| footnotes                       = \n| name                            = \n| image_map1                      = Mili\u0107i-naselja.PNG\n}}\n[[File:Mili\u0107i-naselja.PNG|thumb|472x472px|Settlements of Mili\u0107i municipality]]\n'''Mili\u0107i''' ({{lang-sr-cyrl|\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0438\u045b\u0438}}) is a town and a municipality located in [[Republika Srpska]], an entity of [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. As of 2013, it has a population of 11,441 inhabitants, while the town of Mili\u0107i has a population of 2,368 inhabitants.\n\n==Settlements==\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n* Ba\u010di\u0107i\n* Be\u0161i\u0107i\n* Bijelo Polje\n* Bi\u0161ina\n* Bukovica Donja\n* Bukovica Gornja\n* Buljevi\u0107i\n* Derventa\n* Donje Vrsinje\n* Duba\u010dko\n* Dubnica\n* Duki\u0107i\n* \u0110ile\n* \u0110ur\u0111evi\u0107i\n* Gerovi\n* Glu\u0161ac\n* Goli\u0107i\n* Gornje Vrsinje\n* Gunjaci\n* Jeremi\u0107i\n* Kokanovi\u0107i\n* Koprivno\n* Kostra\u010da\n* Kraj\u010dinovi\u0107i\n* Lukavica\n* Luki\u0107i\n* Ma\u0107esi\n* Mili\u0107i\n* Mi\u0161i\u0107i\n* Nova Kasaba\n* Nuri\u0107i\n* Pavkovi\u0107i\n* Podbira\u010d\n* Podgora\n* Pomol\n* Raji\u0107i\n* Ra\u0161evo\n* Ra\u0161kovi\u0107i\n* Ristijevi\u0107i\n* Rova\u0161i\n* Rupovo Brdo\n* Sebio\u010dina\n* Skugri\u0107i\n* Supa\u010d\n* \u0160tedra\n* Toljevi\u0107i\n* Vi\u0161njica\n* Viti\u0107i\n* Vrto\u010de\n* Vukovi\u0107i\n* Vuk\u0161i\u0107i\n* Zabr\u0111e\n* Zagra\u0111e\n* Zaklopa\u010da\n{{div col end}}\n\n==Demographics==\n\n=== Population ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! colspan=\"6\" 